article.headline: Radford 95, East Tenn. St. 85
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Dan Ross had 30 points and 13 rebounds to lead Radford to a 95-85 win over East Tennessee State Tuesday night. Ross was one of three Radford players to record a double-double: Whit Holcomb-Faye scored 21 with 13 assists, and Chris Oliver had 14 points and 11 rebounds. Kenny Thomas came off the bench to add a career-high 16 points. ETSU (0-2) jumped out to a 10-point lead in the first four minutes. Radford (3-1) brought it to within five, but the Buccaneers pushed the lead to 11 on a 3-pointer from Courtney Pigram. Radford followed with an 18-3 run that included three straight 3-pointers to take the lead 47-39 at the break. Ross had two of his seven 3-pointers during the run. The Buccaneers tied it early in the second half before the Highlanders opened the gap to nine and never looked back. Dillion Sneed led ETSU with 24. Tim Smith added 20, Travis Strong 15 and Pigram 12.
